Cell.Data: Identifies the specification of content and rules that apply to the transaction.
Identifies the BII profile or business process context in which the transaction appears.
The identity of the Receipt Advice set by the sender. It must be a unique identity. The Identity together with the Issue Date and Issue Time gives the version of the Receipt Advice.
The date when the Receipt Advice was issued. Format = "YYYY-MM-DD"
The time when the Receipt Advice is issued. Format = "HH:MM:SS+timezone". Timezone is optional to use. If omitted, the local timezone where the document was issued should be assumed.
A code signifying the status of the Receipt Advice. Default is Original (9)
A code signifying the type of the Receipt Advice - Response to the Advanced Despatch Advice (D) or Response to the received Shipment (S).
A textual note for the delivery as whole.
A reference to the original order
Used to provide a reference to the order on which the despatch is based.
Used to provide a reference to the order on which the despatch is based.
A reference to the Advanced Despatch Advice.
The ID of the Advanced Despatch Advice. The unique identity of the Advanced Despatch Advice is made up by ID, IssueDate and IssueTime in combination.
The date the Advanced Despatch Advice was issued.
The time the Advanced Despatch Advice was issued.
The time when the Advanced Despatch Advice was issued. Format = "HH:MM:SS+timezone". Timezone is optional to use. If omitted, the local timezone where the document was issued should be assumed.

To be used when the Receipt Advice is a response to the received Advanced Despatch Advice. The status Code describes whether the Advanced Despatch Advice is accepted or if it is rejected due to errors, and the supplier should send a new.
Text to describe the reason for the rejection.
The ID of the Advanced Despatch Advice. The unique identity of the Advanced Despatch Advice is made up by ID, IssueDate and IssueTime in combination.
The date the Advanced Despatch Advice was issued.
The time the Advanced Despatch Advice was issued.
The time when the Advanced Despatch Advice was issued. Format = "HH:MM:SS+timezone". Timezone is optional to use. If omitted, the local timezone where the document was issued should be assumed.

To be used when the Receipt Advice is a response to the received Advanced Despatch Advice. The status Code describes whether the Advanced Despatch Advice is accepted or if it is rejected due to errors, and the supplier should send a new.
Text to describe the reason for the rejection.
